---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy — Sneat Club"
  description="How Sneat Club handles your club's information: privacy-first, minor-safe by design, you own your data, and we never sell it."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
      <h1>Your club's people — kept safe, and yours</h1>
      <p>
        A club trusts Sneat Club with something sensitive: its members, including
        children. So privacy isn't an afterthought here; it's the foundation the whole
        product stands on.
      </p>

      <h2>You own your data</h2>
      <p>
        Your club, teams, members, rosters and records belong to your club. They live in
        your own space, and you can review, export and remove them at any time. We ask only
        for what a useful record needs, and we never sell it or mine it for advertising.
      </p>

      <h2>Minor-safe by design</h2>
      <p>
        Children on a roster are protected: a minor player's public details are governed by
        guardian consent, and absent that consent a young player is shown by first name and
        jersey number only. Parents and guardians control what is shared about their child.
      </p>

      <h2>The graph is the club's, not ours</h2>
      <p>
        The relationships that make a club — coach to player, parent to child, member to
        team — are yours. They power reminders, communication and the roster, and they stay
        inside your club's space; they are never rented out.
      </p>

      <h2>This is an early page</h2>
      <p>
        Sneat Club is in active development. This page will grow into a full privacy policy
        as the product launches. Questions in the meantime? Reach us via the
        <a href="https://sneat.co" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sneat platform</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="back"><a href="/">← Back to home</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose { max-width: 720px; }
  .prose h1 { font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 5vw, 2.6rem); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .prose h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; margin-top: var(--space-4); }
  .back { margin-top: var(--space-4); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
